<br>
As a rogue, I'm loving it so far.  Healthy ratio upgrade to my offhand weapon (previously a Fired Velium Warsword, 11/22) even without the magic bonus, a good AC and Dex boost, and largely negligible losses to str and sta (5 points each).  And since ratio in the offhand means everything pretty much, having it slower means I don't taunt as much, which is nice when I've started occasionally taunting off of people 3 or 4 levels my senior ... <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
Not to mention the quest is pretty darn easy to get through.  For the levels needed to kill the creatures in question, someone in their low to mid 40s could do this easy with a group, maybe even lower, and for those levels this weapon is even more killer.<br>
<br>
